{"bill":{"bill_id":1640477,"change_hash":"035f7acc47046c0465ffeb5accb52e70","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB841\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB841","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-06","progress":[{"date":"2022-12-28","event":1},{"date":"2022-12-28","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-01","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-06","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-09","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-13","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-24","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-24","event":2}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB841","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"Alcohol safety action programs.","description":"Alcohol safety action programs. Provides that the membership of a local independent policy board of an alcohol safety action program must include at least one criminal defense attorney who has specialized knowledge in representing persons charged with driving while intoxicated offenses and the local board shall request a local attorney for the Commonwealth to sit on the board. The bill also provides that any court that has convicted a person of a reckless driving violation in which the defendant was initially charged with a driving while intoxicated violation a shall have continuing jurisdiction over such person during any period of license revocation related to that conviction for the limited purposes of (i) referring such person to a certified alcohol safety action program; (ii) providing for a restricted driver's license permit for such person; and (iii) imposing terms, conditions, and limitations for actions related to such person's participation in a certified alcohol safety action program and use of the restricted driver's license permit. As introduced, this bill was a recommendation of the Commission on the Virginia Alcohol Safety Action Program.  Alcohol safety action programs. Provides that the membership of a local independent policy board of an alcohol safety action program must include at least one criminal defense attorney who has specialized knowledge in representing persons charged with driving while intoxicated offenses and the local board shall request a local attorney for the Commonwealth to sit on the board. The bill also provides that any court that has convicted a person of a reckless driving violation in which the defendant was initially charged with a driving while intoxicated violation a shall have continuing jurisdiction over such person during any period of license revocation related to that conviction for the limited purposes of (i) referring such person to a certified alcohol safety action program; (ii) providing for a restricted driver's license permit for such person; and (iii) imposing terms, conditions, and limitations for actions related to such person's participation in a certified alcohol safety action program and use of the restricted driver's license permit. As introduced, this bill was a recommendation of the Commission on the Virginia Alcohol Safety Action Program.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2022-12-28","committee_id":168,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Rehabilitation and Social Services"},{"date":"2023-01-13","committee_id":4165,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Judiciary"},{"date":"2023-02-09","committee_id":150,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Courts of Justice"}],"history":[{"date":"2022-12-28","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23103601D","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2022-12-28","action":"Referred to Committee on Rehabilitation and Social Services","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":